-- Gazprom, Rosneft and Lukoil May Move Today: Russian Stock Market Preview
-- Stephen Bierman
-- 2010-07-07T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/gazprom-rosneft-and-lukoil-may-move-today-russian-stock-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  
 The Micex Index of 30 stocks climbed 2.7 percent to
1,327.63 at the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS
Index rose 2.7 percent to 1,353.66.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): Ukraine’s NAK Naftogaz Ukrainy said
in an e-mailed statement that it paid Russia’s gas export
monopoly $710 million for gas deliveries in June. Gazprom
advanced 2.8 percent to 152.44 rubles.  
 OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil was little changed at
$72.10 a barrel at 1:02 p.m. in New York, paring an earlier gain
of as much as 2.4 percent after President  Barack Obama  said
Isreali Prime Minister  Benjamin Netanyahu  will take “risks for
peace.” Russia’s largest oil producer rose 2.8 percent to
192.89 rubles.  OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX), Russia’s second-largest oil
producer, rose 1.4 percent to 1,604.42 rubles.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        